# Project Structure & Naming Conventions

# Root Directory
- `src/`: Main source code.
- `tests/`: Test suite.
- `docs/`: Project documentation and planning artifacts.
  - `docs/plans/`: Per-phase plan files (NN-name.md). Immutable once started.
  - `docs/PROGRESS.md`: Active plan pointer + chronological journal of completed waves (checkboxes archived from plans after commit).
  - `docs/DECISIONS.md`: Accumulated architectural decisions across all phases.
- `pyproject.toml`: Dependency management via `uv`.

# Source Tree (src/)
- `core/`: Domain models, `AppError` base classes.
  - `core/types.py`: Shared domain types and enums.
  - `core/constants.py`: Domain-level constants only.
- `operations/`: Application use-cases (`search_urls`, fetch page HTML/markdown).
- `adapters/`: Infrastructure (SearXNG HTTP, Playwright pool).
- `mcp_servers/`: MCP transport only (lifespan, tool schema, delegation to operations).

# Naming Rules
- Files: `snake_case`.
- Classes: `PascalCase`.
- Tools (MCP): `verb_noun` (e.g., `get_model_status`).
- Modules: Avoid `utils`, `common` or `helpers`. Use explicit names like `text_processor`, `db_client`.

# Init Files
- `__init__.py`: Keep empty unless explicit re-exports are needed.
  Re-exports only in package-level `__init__.py` (e.g., `src/core/__init__.py`).